details.IncidentDetail: "[160] *****P-2 and P-3 ATTEMPTED TO NEGOTIATE THE FLOODED RDWY FROM THE OTHER SIDE OF P-1, BUT BECAME STUCK IN THE MUD DEBRIS AS WELL****"

"[159] ***********PRELIMINARY INFO FROM INVOLV PARTIES************* (UN-INVOLV) BLACK P-UP and P-1 WERE TRAVEL EB (NORTH) ON US97 SHORTLY BEFORE 0500. AS THEY CAME UPON WHITNEY CREEK, THERE WAS ALLREADY MOVING WATER/MUD WASHING OVER RDWY, AS DRAINAGE RELIEF WAS FILLING QUICKLY, DUE TO LARGE BOULDER PARTIALLY/MOSTLY BLOCKING TUNNEL THAT UNDERCROSSED THE ROADWAY.
BLK PICKUP TRAVERSED ACROSS/THROUGH THE MOVING WATER/DEBRIS AT SLOW SPEEDS and SUCESSFULLY MADE IT ACROSS. AT APPROX THE SAME TIME, P-2 and P-3 WERE DRIVING THEIR RESPECTIVE VEHICLES WB (SOUTH) ON US-97 AND WERE COMING UP ON/APPROACHING WHITNEY CREEK.
AFTER SEEING THE BLACK PICKUP NEGOTIATE THE FLOODED RDWY, P-1 ATTEMPTED TO EXECUTE SAME MANUEVAR WITH HIS FAMILY, BUT BECAME STUCK APPROX HALF-WAY ACROSS, DUE TO THE MUD/DEBRIS/SMALL BOULDERS, WHICH WERE NOW PART OF TEH FLOW - DUE TO THE SPILLWAY BEING BLOCKED BY THE (AFOREMENTIONED) LARGE BOULDER"
